HEADWORD: emaciated
<hw>emaciated</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>having become so thin that the
bones noticeably protrude under the skin; <as>as, <ex>emaciated</ex>
bony hands</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bony, cadaverous, gaunt, haggard, pinched, skeletal,
wasted.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

